<subSubSection id="C34D47CEFFEAC869FF0DBC6DFC46F93B" pageId="20" pageNumber="375" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BE81445FFEAC869FF0DBC6DFC46F93B" blockId="20.[151,1436,1590,2013]" pageId="20" pageNumber="375">
<emphasis id="B923C857FFEAC869FF0DBC6DFEC3F98A" bold="true" box="[151,274,1590,1616]" pageId="20" pageNumber="375">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is close to 
<taxonomicName id="4C576FC6FFEAC869FD8CBC6CFC82F988" authority="(Rondani, 1866)" baseAuthorityName="Rondani" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[534,851,1591,1618]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Drymeia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="375" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brumalis">
<emphasis id="B923C857FFEAC869FD8CBC6CFD48F98B" box="[534,665,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="375">D. brumalis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC669B4FFEAC869FD32BC6CFC9BF988" author="Rondani, C." box="[680,842,1591,1618]" pageId="20" pageNumber="375" pagination="68 - 217" refId="ref14028" refString="Rondani, C. (1866) Anthomyinae Italicae collectae distinctae et in ordinem dispositae [a prof. Camillo Rondani]. Atti della Societa italiana di Scienze naturali, 9, 68 - 217." type="journal article" year="1866">Rondani, 1866</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
which also has 3 postsutural dorsocentrals. However, the male of 
<taxonomicName id="4C576FC6FFEAC869FE86BC00FE71F9AF" baseAuthorityName="Rondani" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[284,416,1627,1653]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Drymeia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="375" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brumalis">
<emphasis id="B923C857FFEAC869FE86BC00FE71F9AF" box="[284,416,1627,1653]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="375">D. brumalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has frontal vitta equal to diameter of anterior ocellus; mid and hind femora with the anteroventral and posteroventral setae longer, denser and more numerous; hind tibia with the anteroventral (and anterior) and posteroventral setae more numerous and dense (only 3–4 posteroventrals and 3 anteroventrals in 
<taxonomicName id="4C576FC6FFEAC869FB5FBCF8FA81F967" authorityName="Pont" authorityYear="2022" box="[1221,1360,1699,1725]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Drymeia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="375" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sororcula">
<emphasis id="B923C857FFEAC869FB5FBCF8FA81F967" box="[1221,1360,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="375">D. sororcula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Both sexes of 
<taxonomicName id="4C576FC6FFEAC869FF6DBC9CFEAAF93B" baseAuthorityName="Rondani" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[247,379,1735,1761]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Drymeia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="375" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brumalis">
<emphasis id="B923C857FFEAC869FF6DBC9CFEAAF93B" box="[247,379,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="375">D. brumalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lack the ventral scutellar setulae of 
<taxonomicName id="4C576FC6FFEAC869FC9FBC9CFC41F93B" authorityName="Pont" authorityYear="2022" box="[773,912,1735,1761]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Drymeia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="375" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sororcula">
<emphasis id="B923C857FFEAC869FC9FBC9CFC41F93B" box="[773,912,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="375">D. sororcula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34D47CEFFEAC868FF5DBCB0FC20FE9B" lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="376" pageId="20" pageNumber="375" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BE81445FFEAC869FF5DBCB0FD69F8F0" blockId="20.[151,1436,1590,2013]" pageId="20" pageNumber="375">
<emphasis id="B923C857FFEAC869FF5DBCB0FE9FF8DF" bold="true" box="[199,334,1771,1797]" pageId="20" pageNumber="375">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C576FC6FFEAC869FDA3BCB0FD75F8DF" authorityName="Pont" authorityYear="2022" box="[569,676,1771,1797]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Drymeia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="375" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sororcula">
<emphasis id="B923C857FFEAC869FDA3BCB0FD75F8DF" box="[569,676,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="375">sororcula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” is Latin and means “little sister”. This reflects the close similarity between this species and 
<taxonomicName id="4C576FC6FFEAC869FE28BD54FD65F8F0" authority="(Rondani)" baseAuthorityName="Rondani" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[434,692,1807,1834]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Drymeia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="375" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brumalis">
<emphasis id="B923C857FFEAC869FE28BD54FDE9F8F3" box="[434,568,1807,1833]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="375">D. brumalis</emphasis>
(Rondani)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
